\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. K. lobata} (Bieb.) Roemer & Schultes,{\i  Syst. Veg.}{\b  2}: 620 (1817) ({\i K. brevis} Steven, {\i K. degenii} Domin). Densely caespitose, forming small, compact tufts. Stems 20-35 cm, with enlarged bulbous bases. Leaves of non-flowering shoots 2-5 cm × 1-1·5 mm, convolute, glaucous, glabrous; sheaths persistent, dilated with parallel or corrugated veins, glabrous. Panicle a short dense spike 20-25 × c. 8 mm. Spikelets 5-7 mm, sessile or shortly pedicellate. Glumes unequal, acuminate, pale green or purplish, scabrid or hairy. Lemma glabrous to slightly hairy, with an apical awn up to 1 mm. 2n = 28.{\i  Dry places. S.E. Europe,from Turkey to S.E. Russia.} Bu Rm Rs (W, K, E) Tu.
