\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 11. K. nitidula} Velen.,{\i  Fl. Bulg.} 611 (1891). Laxly or densely caespitose, with short, creeping rhizomes. Stems 30-40(-65) cm, very slender. Leaves of non-flowering shoots 15-25 cm × c. 1 mm, plicate or flat, glabrous, soft, green or greyish-green; sheaths occasionally breaking down into ribbons when mature, slightly pubescent. Panicle 60-80 × 15-30 mm, narrowly lanceolate and dense when young, ovoid and lax when mature. Spikelets 4-4·5 mm, with long pedicels. Glumes unequal, acute, narrowly lanceolate, bright green and shining, glabrous. Lemma acute or aristate, narrowly lanceolate, hyaline.{\i  Rocky places and dry grassland. C. & E. parts of Balkan peninsula.} ?Au Bu ?Hu Ju Tu.
